<seg id="2">4, 2010: A California family waiting to apply for food stamps at the Sacramento County Economic Development Department in Sacramento, Calif.</seg>
<seg id="3">WASHINGTON - Forty-eight million Americans will have their food stamps benefits slashed starting Friday, when a recession-era boost in the Supplemental Nutrition Assistant Program expires.</seg>
<seg id="4">The move to cut back benefits will be the first wide-scale change to the program affecting nearly every single participant.</seg>
