<doc docid="33573f4d92149bc49307d8e4c12f25e2" genre="news" origlang="xx">
<seg id="1">Robert Porter banned from keeping animals for leaving dogs in car</seg>
<seg id="2">A man who left his two dogs "slowly cooking" inside a hot car in the height of summer has been banned from keeping animals for ten years, the Scottish SPCA has said.</seg>
<seg id="3">The charity said that Robert Porter, 54, of Glencoe Street, Glasgow, was sentenced at Dumbarton Sheriff Court on Thursday following an investigation.</seg>
<seg id="4">Porter left his two Jack Russell terriers in a hot car in the car park of Clydebank Shopping Centre on June 4, 2013.</seg>
<seg id="5">It was one of the hottest days of the year.</seg>
<seg id="6">The dogs survived their ordeal, but could have died, the charity said.</seg>
<seg id="7">In addition to a ban on keeping animals, Porter was given a deprivation order, meaning the dogs will not be returned to his care.</seg>
<seg id="8">Porter was also ordered to pay the charity £250 in compensation.</seg>
<seg id="9">SSPCA Senior Inspector Nicki Scott said that the dogs were showing signs of distress, were panting and had no water.</seg>
<seg id="10">They had to be taken to the vet and treated for heat stress.</seg>
<seg id="11">She said: "It's important to understand that the heat inside a vehicle can build up to a dangerous level when it's warm outside."</seg>
<seg id="12">""The temperature that day was showing as 24 degrees and there was no wind or shade in the car park, therefore the temperature inside the van would have been much higher.</seg>
<seg id="13">Dogs can't sweat the way humans do and they need to pant to cool down.</seg>
<seg id="14">""With the extremely hot air in the vehicle and the lack of water or shade available, the dogs were slowly cooking and they could have died had we not intervened.</seg>
<seg id="15">What makes this case all the more worrying is that one of our inspectors had advised Porter of the dangers of leaving his dogs in his vehicle just weeks before, yet he chose to ignore their welfare needs to go shopping on one of the hottest days of the year.</seg>
<seg id="16">""Porter also changed his story saying that his dogs had been left for only 20 minutes to actually having been left for over an hour and a half.</seg>
<seg id="17">We are pleased Porter has received a ban on keeping animals as, in our opinion, he is unfit to provide proper care.</seg>
<seg id="18">Both dogs will now be found a loving new home.</seg>
</doc>
<doc docid="34e9ee97489b8031940aa6d8a9268e47" genre="news" origlang="xx">
