<seg id="3">AFG has turned selfmockery into a global brand</seg>
<seg id="4">The question AFG Media, a four-year-old British costume maker, wants you to ask yourself the day after Halloween is: Why didn't I dress up as a monster clown in head-to-toe, skin-tight spandex?</seg>
<seg id="5">The clown outfit was the Edinburgh-based company's most popular design this season out of its range of flesh-hugging, face-encasing "morphsuits," which includes an evil surgeon, an elf and a crash-test dummy.</seg>
