<seg id="1">Fears for reef over port developments</seg>
<seg id="2">Threatened: Parts of the Great Barrier Reef, especially areas closer to the mainland, are deteriorating.</seg>
<seg id="3">Much of the Great Barrier Reef is continuing to degrade, especially areas closest to the mainland, where new port developments are awaiting approval from the federal government.</seg>
<seg id="4">The latest strategic assessment of the reef confirmed that, while there were pockets of good news, hard coral had declined by half since 1986 in the bottom two-thirds of the reef, south of Cooktown.</seg>
