<seg id="1">Tinder couple take their romance offline</seg>
<seg id="2">Sydney musician Saraya Beric and Brisbane pilot Peter Williams are a Tinder success story.</seg>
<seg id="3">Picture: Supplied.</seg>
<seg id="4">WHOEVER said Tinder was merely a meat market was mistaken and this loved-up couple is proof.</seg>
<seg id="5">Sydney musician Saraya Beric and Brisbane pilot Peter Williams are up and away after meeting through the social networking app last month.</seg>
<seg id="6">Tinder is a location-based dating app which highlights fellow singles in your area.</seg>
<seg id="7">More than 30 billion profile ratings and 300 million matches have been made through the app, which has been around for just over a year.</seg>
<seg id="8">Saraya, a violinist and performer, says it was love at first swipe for the high-flying couple.</seg>
<seg id="9">I was surprised to meet someone.</seg>
<seg id="10">It started off as a bit of a joke when I was bored.</seg>
<seg id="11">I was in Brisbane hanging out with friends when they grabbed my phone and downloaded the app.</seg>
<seg id="12">We were at a bar and having a few wines so we just started going through everyone.</seg>
<seg id="13">I'm pretty picky and said 'no' to the majority," she said.</seg>
<seg id="14">I said yes to Peter because he looked nice and a few days later he matched back.</seg>
<seg id="15">One of his photos was pretty funny so I said something about it and we just got chatting.</seg>
<seg id="16">We had really good conversation and the same ideas about things so there was common ground there.</seg>
<seg id="17">Get aquainted with Tinder, the dating app of choice for Aussie singles.</seg>
<seg id="18">The 29-year-old - who has works with artists including The McClymonts, Goldfrapp, M-Phazes, 360, Boy & Bear, Illy and Josh Groban - said they took their romance offline and went on a date a week later.</seg>
<seg id="19">When he picked me up I thought he was cute.</seg>
