<seg id="1">Syria Peace Envoy Renews Call for Talks</seg>
<seg id="2">The U.N.-Arab League envoy to Syria ended a days-long visit to Damascus on Friday, calling on both the government and the opposition to attend a peace conference in Geneva later this month but acknowledging the gathering cannot take place if the opposition refuses to take part.</seg>
<seg id="3">Lakhdar Brahimi, who had traveled to Damascus at the end of a Mideast tour to muster regional support for the conference, appeared uncertain about prospects for the meeting.</seg>
<seg id="4">"We will say it's happened only when it happens," he told reporters at a press conference in Damascus, urging both sides to cooperate.</seg>
