<seg id="1">St Joseph's Primary school in Selkirk at 'turning point'</seg>
<seg id="2">A school rated "weak" and "unsatisfactory" by inspectors has reached a "turning point" according to its headteacher.</seg>
<seg id="3">St Joseph's RC in Selkirk was falling below standards in all categories.</seg>
<seg id="4">Inspectors said children had not been "achieving well" but were now starting to "feel better about their learning."</seg>
