<seg id="1">Crash closes key A4232 route into Cardiff</seg>
<seg id="2">1 November 2013 Last updated at 16:55</seg>
<seg id="3">One of the main routes into Cardiff was closed for nearly five hours after a crash between a car and a lorry.</seg>
<seg id="4">Emergency services say the incident happened on the A4232 at 11:45 GMT between the exit from junction 33 of the M4 and the A48 Cowbridge Road West at Culverhouse Cross.</seg>
<seg id="5">The lorry has overturned and is down the embankment but there are no reports of any injuries.</seg>
<seg id="6">One lane remains closed after the road reopened at 16:30 GMT.</seg>
<seg id="7">Motorists were diverted off the M4 at Junction 32 and advised to use the A470 before taking the A48 at Gabalfa to Culverhouse Cross.</seg>
