<seg id="1">The art of the post break-up wardrobe</seg>
<seg id="2">A broken heart need not mean a style hiatus.</seg>
<seg id="3">Here is your guide to looking great post break-up</seg>
<seg id="4">It's been a tough year so far in the love steaks, with some of our favourite couples calling it quits.</seg>
<seg id="5">The incomprehensibly attractive Mirlando (Miranda Kerr and Orland Bloom) are no more, while Julia Restoin Roitfeld and Robert Konjic recently announced that they'd joined the broken hearts club.</seg>
<seg id="6">Then there was Liberty Ross and Rupert Sanders, which of course lead to the break-up of Kristen Stewart and RPatz following Sanders's and Stewart's paparazzi-captured tryst.</seg>
<seg id="7">It's a nasty business that plays havoc on your emotions as well as your outfit choices - (hello, flannel pjyamas)!</seg>
<seg id="8">But once the obligatory Bridget Jones chardonnay/ ice cream/ power ballad moment has passed, it's time to emerge phoenix-like and embrace the world once more.</seg>
<seg id="9">The bevy of newly solo celebs is showing us that a single status means cranking up the stakes when it comes to your wardrobe.</seg>
<seg id="10">Miranda Kerr: Skinny Jeans</seg>
<seg id="11">Miranda is more treat than trick in her skinny jeans.</seg>
<seg id="12">Yes, she has the body of an angel (and a former Victoria's Secret one, at that) who would look phenomenal in almost anything but we can all take note from Miranda's post break-up skinny jean uniform.</seg>
<seg id="13">Paired with a casual T-shirt and pair of heels they say sexy but not try-hard, perfect for that 'accidental meeting' in the ex's local.</seg>
<seg id="14">Trilogy has an excellent range including fashion desk favorites Paige Denim's Hoxton Skinny (trilogystores.co.uk)</seg>
<seg id="15">READ: Orlando Bloom speaks about split from Miranda Kerr</seg>
<seg id="16">Julia Restoin Roitfeld: Leather</seg>
<seg id="17">When French model/muse Julia Restoin Roitfeld stepped out in a leather pencil skirt at the Whitney Museum of American Art Gala mere days after the demise of her relationship the message was clear - wham bam back in the game!</seg>
<seg id="18">READ: Julia Restoin-Roitfeld splits from Robert Konjic</seg>
<seg id="19">Nothing says vampy goddess more than a splash of leather so channel your inner Sandy and don a pair of second skin trousers or a figure-hugging dress.</seg>
<seg id="20">Keep the length long and pair with knitwear, silks and velvets to stay on the right side of chic and steer yourself away from the trashy lane.</seg>
<seg id="21">Liberty Ross: short and sweet</seg>
<seg id="22">Liberty Ross demonstrates leg power in denim shorts Photo: Rex</seg>
<seg id="23">After her separation from husband Rupert Sanders, model Liberty Ross demonstrated the impact of a bit of leg.</seg>
<seg id="24">Flashing well-honed thighs in a pair of micro denim shorts over the summer she appeared anything but a woman scorned.</seg>
<seg id="25">READ: Liberty Ross on Rupert Sanders's and Kristen Stewart's affair</seg>
<seg id="26">Wax, buff and moisturize those pins to perfection then don this season's mini kilt with over-the-knee boots and an aviator jacket.</seg>
<seg id="27">Katie Holmes: killer heels</seg>
<seg id="28">Katie Holmes strikes a pose in sexy slingbacks Photo: Rex</seg>
<seg id="29">As break-up wardrobes go, Katie Holmes is perhaps the queen.</seg>
<seg id="30">When TomKat split she went through nothing short of a transformation as she morphed from she of strained expressions and ballet pumps to a radiant knock-out swishing around town in a succession of fabulous heels.</seg>
<seg id="31">Resigned to a marriage full of flat shoes - one of the many downsides to a diminutive other half (sorry, Tom Cruise) - Katie's liberation made way for Manolos, Choos and Louboutins galore.</seg>
<seg id="32">Empowering and feminine, a pair of killer heels is the fastest way to get your single gal strut back in action.</seg>
<seg id="33">Check out Sophia Webster (sophiawebster.co.uk‎) and Paul Andrew (paulandrew.com‎) for a morale-boosting self-gift.</seg>
</doc>
